      "source": "brake_system_noise.pdf",
      "page": 1,
      "text": "Brake Noise Diagnosis Common brake noise issues include squeaking or grinding sounds. Possible Causes: 1. Worn brake pads 2. Dust accumulation 3. Warped brake rotors 4. Loose brake components Inspection Steps: - Inspect brake pad thickness - Clean brake dust from assembly - Check rotor surface condition - Verify proper installation of components",
